nciThesaurus.definition: A population of allogeneic, cytotoxic natural killer (NK) cells with potential antitumor activity. Allogeneic natural killer cell line MG4101 is derived from cells of a normal, healthy donor upon leukapheresis and activation.
nciThesaurus.preferredName: Allogeneic Natural Killer Cell Line MG4101
synonyms: Allogeneic Natural Killer Cell Line MG4101
